The Chairman of the Senate Committee on Defence and Deputy Chairman, Senate Committee on Anti-Corruption,  Senator Aliyu Magatakarda Wamakko,  has appealed to Nigerians, to join hands with President Muhammadu Buhari,  to move Nigeria to the Next Level of prosperity. The remark  is coming from Wamakko as the nation marks its 59th independence anniversary. The lawmaker who represents Sokoto North Senatorial District in a statement on Monday night by his Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Bashir Rabe Mani  said all well-meaning citizens of the country owe it a duty to the nation,  to render the necessary support, with a view to ensuring the existence of a Nigeria, commensurate to the dreams of all . According to him, “the President is making commendable and plausible efforts to take Nigeria to greater heights.”  